===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a stone beneath a cliff ({{zh-l|*厂}}). The cliff was subsequently distorted into {{zh-l|*丆}}; compare [[叚 ]], [[段]] as well as [[度]], [[席]].

Alternatively, a cave set into the side of a cliff or mountain.

===Etymology 1===
{{unknown|zh}}. 

{{zh-ref|Schuessler, (2007)}} proposes a probable relation {{ncog|mkh-vie-pro|*l-taːʔ||stone}} (whence {{ncog|vi|đá}} and {{ncog|km|ដា||rock; stone}}); however this is unlikely due to both:
* the mismatch between final *-k and *-ʔ, which requires Schuessler to assume that Chinese added "the familiar final ''-k''" after foreign *-ʔ, resulting in *-ʔ-k > *-k (for an analogy, {{och-l|汝|tr=*naʔ}} > {{och-l|若|tr=*nak}}), therefore reducing his proposal's [[parsimony]];
* that so far only nasal pre-initials, not *{{IPAfont|-l-}}, are known to have a voicing effect on Old Chinese voiceless initials (see {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart, 2014}}, {{zh-ref|Jacques, 2020}}, etc.); so Proto-Vietic {{IPAfont|*l-t-}} would unlikely become Old Chinese {{IPAfont|*d-}}.

